OL,7,FLincoln Crown Court heard: "In
OL,8,Fcontrast to what would be expected of
OL,9,Fa reasonable animal shelter, she kept
OL,10,Fnext to no records of the animals and
OL,11,Fany medical treatment they received,
OL,12,Fso much of what she says is a matter
OL,13,Fof assertion.
OL,15,F"We note that she says that she
OL,16,Fcarried the information in her head
OL,17,Fbut also asserts that she is no good
OL,18,Fon dates and times, which would make
OL,19,Fit even less appropriate to keep no
OL,20,Fpaper records."
